race.comment: LUNA ASCENDING (9) peaks and couldn't have been more impressive last time when beaten just 0.6L this track and trip. Settled at the back of the field from the 14 gate and thundered home. Maps for the run of the race today, and has the blinkers applied for the first time. FLAVOURSOME (6) was back to her best, narrowly beaten over 1400m here and then raced an equal favourite over 1800m at Ascot and may have had an excuse. Has to drop back to the sprint but she draws low and the 3kg claim brings her into it. MIDNIGHT STAR (7) resumed here over this distance with a 2L defeat. Was well supported and has more to offer. Has the outside gate to deal with but keeps CJP and that's a positive. The filly FINAL FLUSH (14) resumes and has shown enough to keep very safe. She's trialled well with the race rider aboard and will be naturally improved and push forward.
